INSTABILITY
OF
SPIN
WAVES
AND
MAGNETOSTATIC
MODES
IN
A
MICROWAVE
MAGNETIC
FIELD
APPLIED
PARALLEL
TO
THE
DC
FIELD
TWO
METHODS
OF
CALCULATING
THE
INSTABILITY
THRESHOLD
ARE
DESCRIBED
A
PLANE
WAVE
ANALYSIS
STRICTLY
APPLICABLE
ONLY
IN
AN
INFINITE
MEDIUM
AND
A
MORE
RIGOROUS
THEORY
IN
WHICH
THE
BOUNDARY
CONDITIONS
AT
THE
SURFACE
